#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:254
msgid "Client / Server Design"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:256
msgid ""
"The Emscripten tracing API gathers data from instrumented code and transmits "
"it to a collector server. The server also performs data analysis and "
"provides a web interface for viewing the collected data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:260
msgid ""
"This client / server design is intended to allow the tool to run without "
"interfering with the browser on lower-end hardware where memory might be at "
"a premium, like 32 bit Windows machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:264
msgid ""
"This design also allows for a single server to be run to collect data from a "
"variety of clients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:268
msgid "Data Batching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:270
msgid ""
"Data is batched and sent to the server in chunks, roughly once or twice per "
"second. This avoids having to open a new connection to the server for every "
"single event being recorded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:275
msgid "Do Not Perturb The Heap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:277
msgid ""
"When using the Emscripten tracing API, you should be careful that you do not "
"perform operations that would perturb the heap. For example, you shouldn't "
"allocate a string to pass to :c:func:`emscripten_trace_log_message` as that "
"would result in the allocation being tracked and possibly disturbing the "
"behavior or results that you are trying to analyze."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/trace.h.rst:283
msgid ""
"For this reason, the Emscripten tracing API also keeps all of its own data "
"off of the Emscripten heap and performs no writes to the Emscripten heap."
msgstr ""

